                            <comment id="16069090" author="githubbot" created="Thu, 29 Jun 2017 22:18:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user vahidhashemian opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/3460&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/3460&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5534&quot; title=&quot;KafkaConsumer offsetsForTimes should include partitions in result even if no offset could be found&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-5534&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-5534&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: `offsetForTimes` result should include partitions with no offset&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    For topics that support timestamp search, if no offset is found for a partition, the partition should still be included in the result with a `null` offset value. This `KafkaConsumer` method currently excludes such partitions from the result.&lt;/p&gt;

